Performance workaround for large data validation ranges

After encountering severe performance issues with data validations on large ranges, I found a practical workaround by capping the range size.

The issue occurs in `xform/sheet/data-validations-xform.js` (lines 220-223) when applying data validation to ranges like "T9:T1048576":

```js
const range = new Range(addr);
range.forEachAddress(address => {
  this.model[address] = this._dataValidation;
});
```

however i ran into another issue with styles and e.t.c.. so i decided to work with the xml themselves, maybe i'll try contribute to resolve the issue on this library but for now i will work with the xml files directly without this library.
